A study from the Greek. The motive is taken from the same poem of' Alcaeus that Horace imitated later in C. 1, 9. While snow and rain fall outside‚ the poet calls his friends to celebrate the day with ajar of old wine, so long as youth yet is theirs. As warrant for this he quotes Chiron's advice to his pupil Achilles. Metre‚ 79.
